WEBVTT

00:01.627 --> 00:05.047
[Heather] Every small town
has a secret.

00:05.047 --> 00:08.384
Ours has a game.

00:08.384 --> 00:12.138
The losers stay here where
losing is what we do best.

00:14.140 --> 00:16.142
The winners get out.

00:18.227 --> 00:21.939
In Carp, Texas, out is the only
place worth going.

00:23.190 --> 00:26.527
That's why players
risk their lives to win.

00:26.527 --> 00:30.322
[boy] Victory is yours
if you last until dawn.

00:30.322 --> 00:32.032
Judgment is coming.

00:35.202 --> 00:36.620
[panting]

00:36.620 --> 00:38.289
[lighter striking]

00:41.292 --> 00:43.043
[Heather] But the game
isn't meant to kill you.

00:45.087 --> 00:47.339
And it won't.

00:47.339 --> 00:49.383
If you follow one rule.

00:51.010 --> 00:53.596
Don't panic.

00:53.596 --> 00:55.598
♪ ♪

01:00.102 --> 01:02.104
♪ ♪

01:05.941 --> 01:07.151
[horse neighing]

01:09.195 --> 01:10.488
[Heather] The truth is,

01:10.488 --> 01:13.574
Panic started like
a lot of things out here.

01:13.574 --> 01:15.117
Because it was summer,

01:15.117 --> 01:17.787
and there was
nothing else to do.

01:17.787 --> 01:19.288
-[rapid thudding]
-The games

01:19.288 --> 01:21.665
had always started
right after graduation

01:21.665 --> 01:24.585
and lasted
throughout the summer.

01:24.585 --> 01:28.380
All graduating seniors
are eligible to play.

01:28.380 --> 01:31.675
Sometimes 40 players enter.

01:31.675 --> 01:34.845
Sometimes half that.

01:34.845 --> 01:36.889
But there is only one winner.

01:36.889 --> 01:38.182
[dog barking]

01:38.182 --> 01:42.019
Each year there are new players,

01:42.019 --> 01:44.355
new challenges, new judges.

01:44.355 --> 01:46.023
- [bees buzzing]
- [screams]

01:46.023 --> 01:49.568
But the game has ghosts, too.

01:49.568 --> 01:51.695
♪ Your love feels so fake...

01:51.695 --> 01:54.323
We never have to
say their names.

01:54.323 --> 01:57.243
They know where to find us.

01:57.243 --> 01:59.829
They know we aren't
going anywhere.

01:59.829 --> 02:01.455
[applause]

02:01.455 --> 02:02.998
Not unless we play.

02:02.998 --> 02:07.253
And now, what you've been
waiting for...

02:07.253 --> 02:08.504
the graduates.

02:08.504 --> 02:11.841
- Natalie Williams.
- [boy] Yeah, go, Nat!

02:11.841 --> 02:13.676
[whooping]

02:15.970 --> 02:17.763
Bishop Moore.

02:17.763 --> 02:21.559
♪ Nowhere to go...

02:21.559 --> 02:23.602
Heather Nill.

02:23.602 --> 02:27.147
♪ They've closed the dance
and I've seen the show...

02:27.147 --> 02:28.607
- You're late.
- Fuck you.

02:28.607 --> 02:31.610
[Adam] Hey, Ray, check it out.

02:31.610 --> 02:33.612
I got you a graduation present.
Just something small.

02:33.612 --> 02:36.073
- [Tyler] Yo, let's go.
- What the fuck is this?

02:36.073 --> 02:38.075
It's a "get out of jail free"
card.

02:38.075 --> 02:40.202
[laughs]
What?

02:40.202 --> 02:41.620
I thought it might come in handy

02:41.620 --> 02:42.830
just in case you want
to visit your pops.

02:42.830 --> 02:45.583
- [laughs]
- Yeah? Well...

02:45.583 --> 02:48.085
If only it was
a free pass on herpes.

02:48.085 --> 02:50.004
Then I can bone
Tyler's mom again.

02:50.004 --> 02:51.922
Don't be stupid.
Get out of here.

02:51.922 --> 02:53.841
I can't believe you guys
are skipping the ceremony.

02:53.841 --> 02:56.552
- Well, we are.
- Yahoo!

02:56.552 --> 03:00.014
- [shouts excitedly]
- Let's go.

03:00.014 --> 03:03.017
[whooping, cheering]

03:03.017 --> 03:05.686
Let's go!

03:05.686 --> 03:07.438
[whooping]

03:07.438 --> 03:09.940
♪ ♪

03:15.404 --> 03:18.198
- There's my lady. Hey.
- Hey, Dad.

03:18.198 --> 03:22.369
[band continues playing]

03:22.369 --> 03:23.996
- Speak to you...?
- Yeah.

03:30.294 --> 03:32.421
[photographer] All right.
Father/daughter portrait.

03:32.421 --> 03:35.215
Let's go. Get together.

03:37.176 --> 03:39.678
[camera shutter clicking]

03:39.678 --> 03:42.139
[laughs] Heather!

03:42.139 --> 03:44.058
We're here.

03:44.058 --> 03:45.768
Hi. [chuckles]

03:45.768 --> 03:48.437
- Hi, you.
- Look. Flowers.

03:48.437 --> 03:51.190
Oh, thank you, Lilybug.

03:53.317 --> 03:54.860
Wow, you made it.

03:54.860 --> 03:57.196
Of course I made it.

03:57.196 --> 03:59.198
I'm proud of you.

03:59.198 --> 04:01.659
Here. I got you something.

04:06.372 --> 04:08.707
- Can you hold these for me?
- Sure.

04:15.881 --> 04:17.549
You used to lose your mind
over snow globes.

04:17.549 --> 04:19.051
Couldn't get enough of 'em.

04:19.051 --> 04:21.095
- [chuckles]
- Yeah, I was, like, seven.

04:21.095 --> 04:22.429
One time at the Walmart,
you must have

04:22.429 --> 04:25.307
shook up a hundred
of those things.

04:25.307 --> 04:28.268
I thought I was never gonna
get you out of that store.

04:28.268 --> 04:30.229
Thank you.
It really means a lot.

04:30.229 --> 04:31.981
It's just something little.

04:31.981 --> 04:34.692
You know, mark the occasion
or whatever.

04:37.945 --> 04:40.406
- Why are you looking
at me weird?
- Nothing.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.743
You got 20 bucks?

04:47.329 --> 04:50.040
The car's in the shop again.

04:50.040 --> 04:51.792
Something about the starter.

04:51.792 --> 04:54.920
You know how Bo's truck
eats gas, so...

04:54.920 --> 04:57.548
That's all I got.

04:57.548 --> 04:59.883
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

04:59.883 --> 05:01.427
What happened to
all that back pay

05:01.427 --> 05:02.594
they owe you down at the store?

05:02.594 --> 05:04.805
I can't make them pay me, Mom.

05:09.727 --> 05:11.353
[kisses] Proud of you, kid.

05:15.899 --> 05:18.360
Come on, Lily, let's go.

05:18.360 --> 05:19.903
[Heather] Thank you.

05:19.903 --> 05:21.780
- I'll see you later.
- Love you. Bye.

05:27.661 --> 05:29.872
- Giddyup, bitch, we're free.
- Oh. Hi.

05:29.872 --> 05:32.249
[laughing]

05:33.292 --> 05:34.501
Perfect.

05:36.003 --> 05:37.546
All right, let's get out
of here.

05:37.546 --> 05:40.674
I'm so done with this place.

05:40.674 --> 05:42.634
One... [laughs]

05:42.634 --> 05:44.720
[all] Two, three.

05:44.720 --> 05:46.597
♪ Get ready...

05:46.597 --> 05:48.348
- [cork pops]
- [all cheering]

05:48.348 --> 05:50.517
[laughing]

05:50.517 --> 05:52.519
[overlapping chatter]

06:02.488 --> 06:05.532
♪ ♪

06:07.701 --> 06:10.871
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm. Ah.

06:12.623 --> 06:15.084
What are we toasting?

06:15.084 --> 06:16.210
No more gym.

06:16.210 --> 06:17.795
No more gym shorts.

06:17.795 --> 06:19.338
[Ray] Final collection.

06:19.338 --> 06:22.633
Here we go. Give me your money.

06:22.633 --> 06:23.759
Final collection.

06:23.759 --> 06:26.678
- Here it comes.
- Thank you very kindly.

06:28.847 --> 06:30.682
Final collection.

06:30.682 --> 06:32.226
Rules are rules.

06:32.226 --> 06:36.146
School's out, okay?
I'm-I'm not even playing.

06:36.146 --> 06:39.024
Think of it as insurance.

06:39.024 --> 06:42.152
It's gonna be one hell
of a summer.

06:42.152 --> 06:44.154
Yeah, I mean...

06:44.154 --> 06:47.157
Come on, man, I...
I'm not gonna play.

06:47.157 --> 06:49.368
- Oh, okay!
- We're all playing, fucker.

06:49.368 --> 06:52.079
- [Heather] Ray.
- One way or another.

06:52.079 --> 06:55.332
A dollar buys you a prayer.

06:55.332 --> 06:56.875
[Heather] Ray, stop.

06:56.875 --> 07:00.045
You want your money,
I'm gonna need my arm back.

07:02.005 --> 07:04.299
I'm just fucking with you.
[laughs]

07:06.635 --> 07:08.053
Oh, Bishop.

07:15.936 --> 07:19.148
Hey. A new toast.

07:19.148 --> 07:21.900
To global amnesia.

07:21.900 --> 07:25.821
Nah. Selective.

07:25.821 --> 07:28.323
There's a few things
I want to remember.

07:32.536 --> 07:34.163
[Natalie] Ooh, what did I miss?

07:34.163 --> 07:37.541
Oh, we're-we're toasting to
a future free of Ray Hall.

07:37.541 --> 07:40.127
- Yeah.
- Ugh. That guy sucks.

07:40.127 --> 07:42.004
- Yeah.
- You remember?

07:42.004 --> 07:43.630
Remember when you puked
on the eighth grade field trip?

07:43.630 --> 07:45.257
- Oh.
- Ugh.

07:45.257 --> 07:47.551
- And he spread a rumor
Heather was pregnant.
- Yeah.

07:47.551 --> 07:50.762
And then you told everyone
that he had chlamydia.

07:50.762 --> 07:53.182
- No one messes with my girl.
- Oh...

07:53.182 --> 07:55.434
- To revenge.
- Oh, to chlamydia.

07:55.434 --> 07:57.561
- Oh, no, I'm not toasting that.
- What?

07:57.561 --> 08:00.939
- [Heather chuckles]
- Okay, okay, I got one.

08:00.939 --> 08:03.609
Ready? [laughs]

08:05.777 --> 08:07.613
You-you brought your diploma.

08:07.613 --> 08:08.989
- [Natalie] Of course.
- [Heather] Weird move.

08:08.989 --> 08:10.908
- Ta-da.
- Yeah.

08:10.908 --> 08:12.951
- Oh...
- [Natalie laughs]

08:12.951 --> 08:14.953
- [Heather] What are you doing?
- [Natalie] See? It's toast.

08:14.953 --> 08:16.747
Natalie...

08:16.747 --> 08:18.999
[Natalie] What?
It doesn't matter because...

08:18.999 --> 08:23.253
♪ I'm gonna win Panic ♪♪

08:23.253 --> 08:25.339
Oh, I love this song.
Come on, come on.

08:25.339 --> 08:27.466
- Get up, Heather.
- No. Maybe later.

08:27.466 --> 08:29.092
- [Natalie] No, now.
- [Bishop] No, no, no, no, no.

08:29.092 --> 08:30.636
- Come on, come on.
- Hey, guys...

08:30.636 --> 08:32.721
- It's later now.
- I don't...

08:32.721 --> 08:34.932
I'm not going. Bishop!

08:34.932 --> 08:36.850
We're going, we're going.

08:36.850 --> 08:39.478
What? I can't hear you.

08:39.478 --> 08:42.105
♪ Is this trouble again? ♪

08:42.105 --> 08:46.318
♪ I never had this rush
in my body ♪

08:46.318 --> 08:50.656
♪ I never thought
I'd feel something new ♪

08:50.656 --> 08:54.076
♪ I never felt this close
with somebody ♪

08:54.076 --> 08:56.078
♪ Somebody ♪

08:56.078 --> 08:58.413
♪ Somebody but you ♪

08:58.413 --> 09:02.584
♪ I never felt like this
with somebody ♪

09:02.584 --> 09:06.672
♪ I never thought
I'd feel like I do ♪

09:06.672 --> 09:09.424
♪ I never felt this close
with somebody ♪

09:09.424 --> 09:10.592
- [firecrackers explode]
- [screaming]

09:10.592 --> 09:12.427
[Diggins] Jesus,
what the hell, dude?!

09:12.427 --> 09:14.638
I'm sorry, man, my hand slipped.

09:14.638 --> 09:17.015
- Yeah, onto a lighter.
- My hand slipped.

09:17.015 --> 09:19.935
- But, like, you know...
- The thing is, uh, Dick-ins,

09:19.935 --> 09:22.396
everybody gets a little jumpy
before judgment.

09:22.396 --> 09:24.106
Diggin... Diggins.

09:24.106 --> 09:26.400
Diggins. Diggins.
That's what, that's what I said.

09:26.400 --> 09:28.318
Any word from the judges?

09:28.318 --> 09:30.028
No, I'm just the emcee, okay.

09:30.028 --> 09:32.364
- I'm waiting for the signal
like everybody else.
- Oh.

09:32.364 --> 09:34.157
Well, I better hope
it comes soon.

09:36.660 --> 09:40.580
You know what they say
about idle hands.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.624
[whispers]
It's the devil's workshop.

09:42.624 --> 09:44.543
- [explosion]
- [laughter]

09:46.420 --> 09:49.089
[Ray] Yeah, baby,
get in there, baby...

09:49.089 --> 09:51.633
[door creaks]

10:10.360 --> 10:12.821
[Lily giggles]

10:12.821 --> 10:16.950
It's late, Lilybug.
You should be sleeping.

10:16.950 --> 10:18.577
Why? You're up.

10:18.577 --> 10:20.704
You're stalling.

10:20.704 --> 10:24.541
[sighs] I finished
my library book yesterday.

10:24.541 --> 10:26.877
Mm. Do you want me
to make up a story?

10:29.546 --> 10:30.756
[grunts]

10:32.883 --> 10:38.305
Once upon a time, there was
a town, kind of like ours,

10:38.305 --> 10:42.225
except all of the people
were made of stone.

10:42.225 --> 10:45.812
- Like statues.
- Exactly. Like statues.

10:45.812 --> 10:49.483
And they spoke
with stone tongues

10:49.483 --> 10:53.570
and they waved with stone arms.

10:53.570 --> 10:56.156
Even their hearts
were made of stone.

10:56.156 --> 10:58.658
But one girl was different.

10:58.658 --> 11:02.162
She was made of dirt.

11:02.162 --> 11:05.499
"You're nothing,"
everyone told her.

11:05.499 --> 11:06.708
"Nothing."

11:06.708 --> 11:09.086
Gosh.

11:09.086 --> 11:11.963
And they locked her away
in a high tower,

11:11.963 --> 11:16.051
with no doors,
and only a single window.

11:16.051 --> 11:18.512
Was she lonely?
Was it dark in there?

11:18.512 --> 11:20.847
Yeah.

11:20.847 --> 11:22.474
Yeah, sometimes.

11:24.476 --> 11:28.146
Sometimes she would talk
to the wind to keep her company.

11:28.146 --> 11:31.233
So, how does she escape
out of the high tower?

11:33.235 --> 11:36.238
I don't know.
I haven't gotten that far yet.

11:36.238 --> 11:37.864
Well...

11:37.864 --> 11:40.951
Maybe she makes friends
with a firefly.

11:40.951 --> 11:42.160
Hmm.

11:42.160 --> 11:44.538
You know, maybe
it helps her at night

11:44.538 --> 11:47.165
so she isn't too afraid
of the dark.

11:47.165 --> 11:49.543
You know what?
I think that that's the ending.

11:49.543 --> 11:51.086
I think that's exactly
what happens.

11:51.086 --> 11:52.462
[laughs softly]

11:53.922 --> 11:56.216
Good night. Love you.

11:56.216 --> 11:57.551
- Mwah.
- [chuckles]

11:57.551 --> 11:59.553
- Good night.
- Night.

12:12.649 --> 12:14.651
[exhales]

12:15.694 --> 12:19.030
[dog barking in distance]

12:19.030 --> 12:21.658
♪ ♪

12:26.788 --> 12:28.915
Heather, it's 8:00!

12:28.915 --> 12:32.002
- You're gonna be late for work.
- Okay.

12:32.002 --> 12:34.004
♪ ♪

12:55.275 --> 12:58.028
[Danny] I know you've been
with us for a long time,

12:58.028 --> 13:00.697
but I don't have enough spots
on the schedule.

13:02.699 --> 13:04.326
But you know I'm, like,
I'm the only one

13:04.326 --> 13:08.371
who does anything around here,
really, and...

13:08.371 --> 13:10.707
And I-I've technically been here
longer than you.

13:10.707 --> 13:13.293
Look, a smart girl like you,
you're gonna have no trouble

13:13.293 --> 13:15.378
- finding another gig.
- Please, Danny, I r...

13:15.378 --> 13:17.380
I really, really need this job.

13:17.380 --> 13:19.049
I'm sorry, Heather.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.012
Starting when?

13:24.012 --> 13:27.140
I can get you all squared up
for last week.

13:38.235 --> 13:40.237
♪ ♪

13:50.497 --> 13:52.916
Thank you.

13:52.916 --> 13:56.294
He said that they couldn't
afford to keep me.

13:56.294 --> 13:59.172
But you're the only one
who ever actually does anything.

13:59.172 --> 14:01.174
That's what I said.

14:03.343 --> 14:05.762
I'm sorry, Heather.

14:05.762 --> 14:08.557
You'll find something else.

14:10.725 --> 14:13.144
I need $6,000 to enroll
in the accounting course

14:13.144 --> 14:16.022
- at Longhorn State.
- Jesus. $6,000?

14:16.022 --> 14:17.440
Why do you think
I've been working there

14:17.440 --> 14:19.234
- since freshman year?
- I thought you liked,

14:19.234 --> 14:21.861
you know, unplugging things
and plugging things back in...

14:21.861 --> 14:24.364
[stammers] This is serious.

14:24.364 --> 14:26.825
I was on track to have
the money by orientation.

14:26.825 --> 14:29.578
I only need, like, $500, but...

14:29.578 --> 14:31.663
$500? I-I can spot you that.

14:31.663 --> 14:35.166
I'm not taking your money.

14:35.166 --> 14:38.795
I still have till August
to make the final payment.

14:38.795 --> 14:40.505
I'll figure
something out, right?

14:40.505 --> 14:41.965
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah.

14:43.216 --> 14:44.634
[Bishop] Hey.

14:44.634 --> 14:47.012
- Two minutes. Mm-hmm.
- Thank you.

14:47.012 --> 14:48.888
- All right.
- Thank you.

14:48.888 --> 14:53.602
Hey, so, are you sure about
this whole accounting thing?

14:53.602 --> 14:55.854
Uh, yeah.
When I get my associate's,

14:55.854 --> 14:58.148
I can start clerking at double
what my mom makes hourly.

14:58.148 --> 14:59.649
Heather, you don't
even like math.

14:59.649 --> 15:01.276
Accounting isn't only math.

15:01.276 --> 15:02.986
True, it's also
boring paperwork.

15:02.986 --> 15:05.614
O-Okay, fine.

15:05.614 --> 15:07.198
[stammers]

15:07.198 --> 15:08.908
You're a great writer, Heather.

15:08.908 --> 15:12.329
I mean, you should at least
apply for a scholarship.

15:12.329 --> 15:13.872
[sighs] Yeah, well, they don't
really give out scholarships

15:13.872 --> 15:15.498
for knowing how to make shit up.

15:15.498 --> 15:17.000
Hey, y'all. I got a break.

15:17.000 --> 15:18.376
- [chuckles]
- She's got a break.

15:18.376 --> 15:21.212
Let's do it.

15:21.212 --> 15:23.548
He fired you?
But you're the only one who...

15:23.548 --> 15:25.550
[both] Whoever actually
does anything!

15:25.550 --> 15:26.926
- All right.
- Yes, yes, yes, yes.

15:26.926 --> 15:28.720
I'm sorry, Heather.

15:28.720 --> 15:31.056
- Want me to poison him?
- You know, as much

15:31.056 --> 15:33.933
as that idea excites me, I do
not know how we'd pull that off.

15:33.933 --> 15:36.478
Well, I do refill
his prescriptions.

15:36.478 --> 15:37.937
That's kind of dark.

15:37.937 --> 15:39.147
[cashier] That'll be $4.50.

15:39.147 --> 15:41.441
Well, when I win Panic,

15:41.441 --> 15:43.401
- we don't have
to worry about jobs.
- [Heather sighs]

15:43.401 --> 15:45.862
What did I tell you, right?
She's serious.

15:45.862 --> 15:47.322
You guys should be
rooting for me.

15:47.322 --> 15:49.658
People died last year, Natalie.

15:49.658 --> 15:53.703
I mean, people die in bathtubs,
and in car accidents.

15:53.703 --> 15:55.330
Yeah, especially when
they're walking blindfolded

15:55.330 --> 15:56.539
across the freeway.

15:57.791 --> 15:59.376
I can't lose you, Natalie.

15:59.376 --> 16:01.169
Hey, you couldn't get
rid of me if you tried.

16:01.169 --> 16:04.339
[laughs]
You know, besides,

16:04.339 --> 16:05.882
who is going to keep me grounded

16:05.882 --> 16:08.176
when I'm a rich
and famous actress?

16:08.176 --> 16:09.719
Oh, I can think of two people.

16:10.762 --> 16:13.390
All right, so let's recap.

16:13.390 --> 16:16.142
You are moving to Hollywood
and you are going to college

16:16.142 --> 16:17.644
and I am just gonna
live here forever.

16:17.644 --> 16:19.729
Are you saying
that you're gonna miss us?

16:19.729 --> 16:22.148
- Is that what this is?
- What I'm saying

16:22.148 --> 16:24.401
is that you two losers
are abandoning me.

16:24.401 --> 16:26.403
Mm.

16:29.656 --> 16:31.658
♪ ♪

16:45.004 --> 16:47.006
♪ ♪

17:02.897 --> 17:04.733
Menu?

17:04.733 --> 17:07.944
Um, a Coke, please.

17:20.373 --> 17:21.624
Thanks.

17:23.626 --> 17:26.838
You're, um, Heather, right?

17:26.838 --> 17:28.256
Dodge.

17:28.256 --> 17:31.509
Um, yeah, I know who you are.

17:31.509 --> 17:33.219
You're the new guy.

17:33.219 --> 17:35.221
Well, it's been a year.

17:35.221 --> 17:36.639
[laughs softly]

17:36.639 --> 17:38.641
Everyone here has known
each other from diapers,

17:38.641 --> 17:40.769
so the new guy
is pretty big news.

17:40.769 --> 17:43.396
- Right.
- When nothing
happens around here.

17:43.396 --> 17:46.107
Right.

17:46.107 --> 17:50.487
In fact, Carp is actually
the capital of nothing.

17:50.487 --> 17:52.489
Nothing happening,
nothing changing,

17:52.489 --> 17:54.574
nothing you want to see or do.

17:54.574 --> 17:57.410
What about Panic?

17:58.453 --> 18:00.663
There is no such thing.

18:03.166 --> 18:04.459
Then how'd those two kids die

18:04.459 --> 18:05.752
- last summer?
- Whoa. Keep your voice down,

18:05.752 --> 18:07.879
- for fuck's sake.
- Oh, so it is real.

18:07.879 --> 18:10.298
You know, I thought Ray was
just shaking me down at first.

18:10.298 --> 18:12.550
"A dollar a day, every day
that school is in session."

18:12.550 --> 18:14.427
But then when I saw
that everyone else

18:14.427 --> 18:16.596
had to pay in...

18:16.596 --> 18:18.515
So, how does it work?
When does it start?

18:18.515 --> 18:22.143
You wait for the judges
to send out a signal.

18:22.143 --> 18:23.770
- It's different every year.
- Hmm, and what,

18:23.770 --> 18:25.897
we're just supposed
to wait until then?

18:25.897 --> 18:28.858
[chuckles] Yeah.
I mean, we're really...

18:28.858 --> 18:31.194
supposed to kind of
forget about it.

18:31.194 --> 18:34.197
- Why?
- We're not supposed
to talk about it.

18:34.197 --> 18:35.865
The cops know about the game now

18:35.865 --> 18:38.284
and they know that Jimmy
and Abby were competing.

18:38.284 --> 18:40.620
You could get in trouble
for just watching.

18:40.620 --> 18:42.080
I don't want to watch.
I want to play.

18:43.414 --> 18:45.542
- So what happens next?
- [door bell jingles]

18:45.542 --> 18:47.460
[sighs]

18:47.460 --> 18:50.046
[door closes]

18:50.046 --> 18:51.297
[Dodge] Hey.

18:51.297 --> 18:52.507
Hey.

18:54.509 --> 18:57.512
- Miss Nill.
- Sheriff.

18:57.512 --> 19:00.139
Dodge.

19:00.139 --> 19:02.892
May I, uh, sit
with the cool kids?

19:04.394 --> 19:06.437
Go for it.

19:06.437 --> 19:08.731
[stool scrapes]

19:08.731 --> 19:10.775
[sighs]

19:10.775 --> 19:12.193
[Cortez] Where's your mom,
Dodge?

19:12.193 --> 19:13.653
She's working the night shift.

19:13.653 --> 19:15.488
Can I get you something?

19:15.488 --> 19:17.448
Let me get a root beer.

19:17.448 --> 19:20.285
- What the hell?
- Yeah.

19:20.285 --> 19:22.662
[soft laughter]

19:22.662 --> 19:24.873
Huh.

19:24.873 --> 19:27.083
You job hunting, huh?

19:27.083 --> 19:29.085
Begging.

19:29.085 --> 19:30.420
You know, I'll bet your luck's
gonna change

19:30.420 --> 19:32.088
when they finish the warehouse.

19:32.088 --> 19:34.090
I keep hearing they're gonna
break ground any day, so...

19:34.090 --> 19:35.592
[chuckles]

19:35.592 --> 19:37.594
They've been
"breaking ground any day"

19:37.594 --> 19:39.178
since I was in eighth grade.

19:39.178 --> 19:41.180
[chuckles] Yeah.

19:43.099 --> 19:44.684
Well, good luck.

19:44.684 --> 19:47.729
Okay. Better get back to it.

19:51.065 --> 19:53.067
♪ ♪

20:01.701 --> 20:03.828
- [laughter]
- [Tyler] What the fuck?

20:03.828 --> 20:06.122
- We should build a houseboat.
- Dipshit.

20:06.122 --> 20:07.749
That way we could live
wherever we want.

20:07.749 --> 20:09.500
Wouldn't be a very long life,

20:09.500 --> 20:11.628
if I was stuck on a boat
with you dumb shits.

20:11.628 --> 20:14.505
[Adam] You know, Ray,
that hurts my feelings.

20:14.505 --> 20:16.341
- Honestly.
- Oh, Jesus. Really?

20:16.341 --> 20:17.508
You want a tissue?

20:17.508 --> 20:20.261
[Tyler] Y-Y'all know
there's places

20:20.261 --> 20:22.180
on the ocean
where murder's legal?

20:22.180 --> 20:24.182
- What?
- [laughter]

20:25.516 --> 20:27.560
[Tyler] Why is that funny?
It's international waters,

20:27.560 --> 20:29.729
- bro.
- [Ray] Buddy,

20:29.729 --> 20:31.731
for a drug dealer, uh,

20:31.731 --> 20:33.608
you're pretty terrible
at handling drugs.

20:33.608 --> 20:35.610
Yeah, Tyler, you trying to roll
that thing or make it

20:35.610 --> 20:37.737
- your girlfriend?
- Mm, I don't know.
Aren't you the expert?

20:37.737 --> 20:39.238
[Adam and Ray oohing]

20:39.238 --> 20:40.740
[laughter]

20:47.163 --> 20:48.831
Whoa. Look at this.

20:48.831 --> 20:50.708
White trash.

20:52.710 --> 20:55.046
[Tyler] Could be your mom.

20:55.046 --> 20:56.923
[Tyler laughs]

20:56.923 --> 20:59.008
[Sarah] What? What is it?

21:01.469 --> 21:03.513
It's starting.

21:06.432 --> 21:08.434
♪ ♪

21:18.319 --> 21:19.779
[distant explosion]

21:22.949 --> 21:24.951
[fireworks popping]

21:34.127 --> 21:35.336
[lock clicks]

21:43.928 --> 21:46.556
♪ ♪

21:51.686 --> 21:54.397
[fireworks continue popping]

21:58.109 --> 22:01.904
[woman on TV] That's right.
They are absolutely gorgeous.

22:01.904 --> 22:04.657
Look at those.

22:04.657 --> 22:07.410
- What's wrong with the door?
- Summertime bloat.

22:07.410 --> 22:10.538
You gotta muscle it.

22:10.538 --> 22:13.750
How'd it go?

22:13.750 --> 22:16.711
Absolutely amazing.

22:16.711 --> 22:18.212
That bad, huh?

22:18.212 --> 22:19.881
[woman on TV] This is unlike
anything I have ever...

22:19.881 --> 22:21.716
Yeah, I tried everywhere
on Main.

22:21.716 --> 22:24.385
No one's even really hiring.

22:24.385 --> 22:27.889
Yeah, well,
that's real life, baby.

22:27.889 --> 22:29.849
Just kicks you in the ass.

22:29.849 --> 22:32.268
[phone ringing]

22:32.268 --> 22:33.978
Phone's ringing.

22:33.978 --> 22:35.271
[woman on TV] What do we
have left here?

22:35.271 --> 22:37.273
Seventy... five. Is that right?

22:37.273 --> 22:40.651
[woman 2] That's right,
Sharon, only 75 minutes left,

22:40.651 --> 22:41.819
so get yours...

22:41.819 --> 22:45.490
- Nat, what's up?
- It's on.

22:45.490 --> 22:47.241
What is?

22:47.241 --> 22:48.534
What do you think?

22:48.534 --> 22:50.453
Opening ceremonies
at Pilot's Point.

22:50.453 --> 22:53.498
Damn, and here I thought Fourth
of July came early this year.

22:53.498 --> 22:55.374
- Are you really not coming?
- I can't, Nat.

22:55.374 --> 22:57.710
I would have a heart attack
just watching.

22:57.710 --> 22:59.921
Oh, God, you might be
the first person ever

22:59.921 --> 23:01.464
too afraid to even watch Panic.

23:05.551 --> 23:07.053
You want me to win, right?

23:09.305 --> 23:11.516
Always.

23:11.516 --> 23:13.935
I just don't want you to play.

23:15.937 --> 23:17.772
[siren wailing]

23:19.273 --> 23:20.900
[Cortez] All right,
Langley, Williams,

23:20.900 --> 23:23.361
the fireworks show is back.

23:23.361 --> 23:26.072
Only this time,
coming in from the north.

23:26.072 --> 23:28.074
[Langley] I don't
see them at the west fields.

23:28.074 --> 23:29.951
[Cortez] Let's meet
at the boatyard, all right?

23:29.951 --> 23:32.245
All right, I'll meet you there.

23:32.245 --> 23:34.747
[tires screeching]

23:34.747 --> 23:37.166
[siren wailing]

23:37.166 --> 23:39.085
I'm on my way.

23:42.880 --> 23:45.466
Actually, scratch the boatyard.

23:45.466 --> 23:47.385
All right, now they're
coming in from the south.

23:47.385 --> 23:49.637
What the fuck is going on?

23:49.637 --> 23:51.347
[Williams] Hey,
Langley, I'm over at

23:51.347 --> 23:52.890
the Calhoun Preservation.
Nothin' doin'.

23:52.890 --> 23:55.226
Hey, y'all, I can't get a read
on 'em, they're everywhere.

23:55.226 --> 23:56.811
[tires screech]

23:56.811 --> 23:59.647
[siren wailing]

23:59.647 --> 24:01.607
[fireworks continue popping]

24:01.607 --> 24:04.443
Last time I saw any fireworks
was right by Siskiyou Falls,

24:04.443 --> 24:08.656
so... let's just meet
at the turnoff.

24:11.117 --> 24:14.370
♪ ♪

24:14.370 --> 24:18.166
[excited chatter]

24:18.166 --> 24:21.669
♪ You can holler, you can wail,
you can swing, you can flail ♪

24:21.669 --> 24:23.421
♪ You can fuck
like a broken sail...

24:23.421 --> 24:26.174
[Summer] Phones.

24:26.174 --> 24:27.758
Phones.

24:27.758 --> 24:29.719
You got a phone?
Thank you.

24:29.719 --> 24:31.846
All right.
Don't take this off.

24:31.846 --> 24:35.099
Phone. Thanks.

24:35.099 --> 24:37.393
All right.

24:37.393 --> 24:38.769
Thank you.

24:38.769 --> 24:41.272
♪ ♪

24:41.272 --> 24:43.441
[indistinct chatter]

24:43.441 --> 24:45.401
I'm not letting you
jump off that ledge

24:45.401 --> 24:47.278
looking like a giant condom.

24:47.278 --> 24:49.447
You're not on the swim team
anymore, Toto.

24:49.447 --> 24:51.365
♪ I could never get back up ♪

24:51.365 --> 24:55.453
♪ When the future starts
so slow ♪

24:55.453 --> 24:57.830
♪ You can swing, you can flail ♪

24:57.830 --> 25:00.875
♪ You can blow what's left
of my right mind ♪

25:00.875 --> 25:03.294
♪ I don't mind ♪

25:03.294 --> 25:05.379
♪ You can blow what's left
of my right mind ♪

25:05.379 --> 25:07.381
Hey.

25:07.381 --> 25:10.134
♪ You can blow what's left
of my right mind...

25:10.134 --> 25:12.803
[Diggins over bullhorn] May I
have your attention?

25:12.803 --> 25:14.388
Welcome to Panic.

25:14.388 --> 25:17.433
[all cheering]

25:17.433 --> 25:19.060
My name is Diggins,

25:19.060 --> 25:21.771
and this summer I will be
your host with the most.

25:21.771 --> 25:24.232
This year, the winner of Panic
is gonna take home

25:24.232 --> 25:28.819
the grand prize of $50,000.

25:28.819 --> 25:31.405
[all cheering]

25:31.405 --> 25:33.241
Holy shit. Holy shit.

25:33.241 --> 25:35.076
That's the biggest pot ever.
Last year was only 30.

25:35.076 --> 25:37.286
You all know the rules.

25:37.286 --> 25:39.372
What happens at a challenge
stays at a challenge,

25:39.372 --> 25:41.165
so I don't want to see
any posting,

25:41.165 --> 25:43.834
tweeting or gramming about it,
no exceptions.

25:43.834 --> 25:46.462
Anyone found in violation

25:46.462 --> 25:49.548
risks losing game privileges.

25:49.548 --> 25:53.844
The first challenge is the Jump.

25:53.844 --> 25:56.347
[cheering, whooping]

25:56.347 --> 25:58.432
Remember, kids,

25:58.432 --> 26:02.853
you want to go out and down
into the swimming hole.

26:02.853 --> 26:06.565
You miss it, and it's gonna be
the rocks that break your fall.

26:06.565 --> 26:08.234
Take the leap from the Lookout

26:08.234 --> 26:10.486
and grab yourself 100 points,

26:10.486 --> 26:13.489
courtesy of this year's
friendly judges,

26:13.489 --> 26:16.617
whoever they may be.

26:16.617 --> 26:18.911
Let the games begin!

26:18.911 --> 26:21.247
[all cheering]

26:21.247 --> 26:23.207
That's my cue.

26:23.207 --> 26:25.209
♪ ♪

26:27.211 --> 26:29.964
You know, I have the same suit.

26:29.964 --> 26:32.174
- Wish me luck.
- I wish you wouldn't.

26:32.174 --> 26:33.426
[Summer] Who needs a number,
everyone?

26:33.426 --> 26:36.012
You playing tonight?
You need a number.

26:36.012 --> 26:38.264
Jumping off a cliff?
You need a number.

26:38.264 --> 26:40.391
- Hey, what's up?
- Mimi.

26:40.391 --> 26:43.060
Mimi, that's right.
Mimi, number six.

26:43.060 --> 26:45.980
Best of luck.
Take a flare. Hey, what's up?

26:45.980 --> 26:48.816
Okay, you are number seven.

26:48.816 --> 26:50.443
You are number eight, Matt.
Take a flare.

26:50.443 --> 26:53.321
[♪ The Black Angels:
"Black Grease"]

26:53.321 --> 26:57.074
♪ You're a storm,
so emotional...

26:57.074 --> 26:59.952
- Sorry, go ahead.
- Thanks.

26:59.952 --> 27:01.996
Hit me.

27:01.996 --> 27:04.332
Okay, Natalie, you're number 11.

27:04.332 --> 27:05.916
Take a flare.

27:05.916 --> 27:07.168
Good luck.

27:07.168 --> 27:09.128
♪ You're all right ♪

27:09.128 --> 27:13.257
♪ You come to me in times...

27:13.257 --> 27:14.717
- [Summer] Dodge, right?
- Yep.

27:14.717 --> 27:15.968
You're number 12.

27:15.968 --> 27:19.180
♪ I'm not the kindest guy ♪

27:19.180 --> 27:22.308
♪ But I give, give,
give, give...

27:25.811 --> 27:28.230
[shouts, grunts]

27:28.230 --> 27:31.067
[all cheering]

27:31.067 --> 27:35.196
Contestant number one,
announce yourself.

27:35.196 --> 27:37.406
You know my name, Diggins!

27:37.406 --> 27:40.159
Your mom screams it every night!

27:40.159 --> 27:41.994
[laughter, jeering]

27:41.994 --> 27:44.622
Fuck yeah, that's my boy!

27:44.622 --> 27:47.625
Okay, Ray Hall for the win!

27:47.625 --> 27:50.002
Whoo-hoo!

27:54.215 --> 27:57.927
[all cheering]

27:57.927 --> 28:00.554
Whoo! Yeah!

28:00.554 --> 28:01.639
[Ray] Yeah, baby!

28:01.639 --> 28:04.767
[cheering continues]

28:04.767 --> 28:07.645
Ray Hall for the fucking win,
baby!

28:07.645 --> 28:09.563
Yeah!

28:09.563 --> 28:11.232
Yeah, that wasn't bad.

28:11.232 --> 28:12.858
[laughter, cheering]

28:12.858 --> 28:14.402
[Diggins] He said it,
so I don't have to,

28:14.402 --> 28:18.114
but I will anyway; the one
and only Ray Hall is in!

28:18.114 --> 28:19.740
[all cheering]

28:19.740 --> 28:23.494
♪ ♪

28:23.494 --> 28:27.164
[TV playing indistinctly]

28:27.164 --> 28:30.751
Mom, have you seen all my stuff
for Longhorn State?

28:30.751 --> 28:33.587
What stuff?

28:33.587 --> 28:35.172
Everything.

28:35.172 --> 28:37.383
Information packets,
the course offerings,

28:37.383 --> 28:40.928
- the payment forms.
- Payment forms? [laughs]

28:40.928 --> 28:43.305
Ain't accountants supposed to
teach you how to save money?

28:43.305 --> 28:45.141
[Sherri laughs]

28:45.141 --> 28:46.767
[Heather sighs]

28:46.767 --> 28:49.353
-It was all right here
on the counter.
-I don't know,

28:49.353 --> 28:50.771
your sister was making a mess
of drawings up there

28:50.771 --> 28:53.732
the other day; maybe it got
put away with her stuff.

28:53.732 --> 28:55.609
[woman on TV] ...wear these
pink diamond earrings.

28:55.609 --> 28:56.944
Oh, my goodness.

28:56.944 --> 28:58.821
[continues indistinctly]

29:18.424 --> 29:20.718
[TV playing indistinctly]

29:20.718 --> 29:22.720
♪ ♪

29:31.145 --> 29:32.771
What the fuck?

29:43.073 --> 29:44.867
Fuck, fuck, fuck,
fuck, fuck, fuck.

29:44.867 --> 29:46.619
[women laughing on TV]

29:46.619 --> 29:49.622
[indistinct chatter on TV]

29:54.960 --> 29:56.795
You find it?

29:58.964 --> 30:00.758
You stole my money.

30:05.304 --> 30:09.141
Yeah, it turns out my car
needed a new transmission.

30:09.141 --> 30:10.684
I swear to God,

30:10.684 --> 30:12.186
if I ever find that piece
of shit who sold it to me...

30:12.186 --> 30:15.481
Mom, that money was for school.

30:15.481 --> 30:18.359
- Yeah, well, I need my car
for work, so...
- I don't, I don't give a fuck.

30:18.359 --> 30:20.444
I have been saving
for years, Mom.

30:20.444 --> 30:22.196
Good for you.

30:22.196 --> 30:25.241
Between paying bills and keeping
a damn roof over our heads,

30:25.241 --> 30:28.744
I never seem to have
a dollar to spare.

30:28.744 --> 30:32.373
100%. Except on, like, beer
and lottery tickets

30:32.373 --> 30:33.666
and cigarettes and drugs

30:33.666 --> 30:35.084
- and...
- Watch yourself.

30:35.084 --> 30:38.837
- You had no right...
- You are living in my house.

30:38.837 --> 30:41.799
- That money was mine.
- You are wearing the clothes
I bought you!

30:41.799 --> 30:44.343
- You had no right.
- You are eating the food
I paid for!

30:44.343 --> 30:46.804
What fucking food?

30:53.394 --> 30:56.063
I'm doing my best here, Heather.

30:58.315 --> 31:00.943
It may not look like it, but...

31:03.779 --> 31:06.699
You think you can do better,

31:06.699 --> 31:08.742
you can just walk
right out that door

31:08.742 --> 31:12.121
and find out for yourself
just how easy it is.

31:26.635 --> 31:28.637
♪ ♪

31:47.948 --> 31:49.199
Back with my apology?

32:05.841 --> 32:07.051
Where you going?

32:08.677 --> 32:10.804
- Hey, that's my car.
- Yeah?

32:10.804 --> 32:12.806
Well, it's got
my transmission in it.

32:15.643 --> 32:17.561
[door closes]

32:28.572 --> 32:31.450
♪ ♪

32:46.048 --> 32:48.050
[cheering in distance]

32:59.895 --> 33:03.357
[Diggins] Contestant number 11,
state your name!

33:06.902 --> 33:08.529
Look, you're gonna have to jump

33:08.529 --> 33:11.156
or get down
because we got people who've got

33:11.156 --> 33:13.075
- to get up there.
- For fuck's sake, Diggins,

33:13.075 --> 33:14.868
just give me a minute, okay?!

33:14.868 --> 33:17.996
That's Natalie Williams,
ray of sunshine.

33:17.996 --> 33:20.457
- Go, Natalie! Just go for it!
- Natalie, go!

33:20.457 --> 33:22.626
[boy] Come on, Nat!

33:33.345 --> 33:35.347
[cheering]

33:38.726 --> 33:41.687
[Diggins] Ladies and gentlemen,
we have another one.

33:49.778 --> 33:52.322
Ooh. Hot damn.

33:52.322 --> 33:54.783
Looks like we got a player
trying for the High Point.

33:54.783 --> 33:56.201
- [boy] Yeah!
- [whooping]

33:56.201 --> 33:59.580
- Ooh.
- Who the hell is that?

34:08.464 --> 34:10.382
[Diggins] For all you virgins
out there,

34:10.382 --> 34:12.718
a quick reminder:
a jump from the High Point

34:12.718 --> 34:15.012
will get you a 25-point bonus.

34:15.012 --> 34:18.640
How about a jump
from Devil's Drop?

34:18.640 --> 34:21.393
And for anyone, uh,
dumb or drunk enough

34:21.393 --> 34:23.061
for some questionable
life choices,

34:23.061 --> 34:25.773
there's always Devil's Drop.

34:25.773 --> 34:28.901
A jump from the Drop
will get you an extra 50 points,

34:28.901 --> 34:31.528
and immunity in a challenge
of your choice.

34:43.916 --> 34:47.628
Contestant number 12,
state your name!

34:55.511 --> 34:58.347
- State your...
- Dodge Mason.

35:09.942 --> 35:10.984
[cheering]

35:10.984 --> 35:12.528
[Diggins] That's player 12,

35:12.528 --> 35:15.155
making it look easy
from the high jump.

35:15.155 --> 35:17.282
Way to raise the stakes, Dodge.

35:17.282 --> 35:20.035
♪ ♪

35:20.035 --> 35:22.162
Oh, shit.

35:22.162 --> 35:24.164
What the fuck was that?

35:25.207 --> 35:29.002
♪ So we party
when the sun goes low ♪

35:29.002 --> 35:32.881
♪ Imminent annihilation
sounds so dope ♪

35:32.881 --> 35:36.718
♪ I'm not shy
but I refuse to speak ♪

35:36.718 --> 35:41.348
♪ Because I don't trust you
to understand me ♪

35:41.348 --> 35:47.104
♪ You know me as the girl
who plays with fire ♪

35:47.104 --> 35:53.193
♪ But this is the song
I wrote you in the dark ♪

35:53.193 --> 35:55.696
♪ I hear they're calling
my name ♪

35:55.696 --> 36:01.827
♪ I'm not gonna sleep anymore...

36:01.827 --> 36:04.329
[excited chatter]

36:04.329 --> 36:06.582
[Diggins] Contestant 22,
you're up.

36:06.582 --> 36:08.041
[Natalie] You went
for the high jump.

36:08.041 --> 36:11.169
- Yeah.
- Were you scared?

36:11.169 --> 36:13.547
To jump? No.

36:13.547 --> 36:16.174
It's the landing
that gets you in trouble.

36:16.174 --> 36:18.343
- [chuckles] Yeah.
- Yeah.

36:18.343 --> 36:22.222
- You want a...?
- No, I'm...

36:22.222 --> 36:24.224
Heather?

36:30.355 --> 36:31.899
What are you doing here?

36:31.899 --> 36:33.150
[Heather] I tried to call you.

36:33.150 --> 36:34.943
Why are you in a bathing suit?

36:36.945 --> 36:39.948
I guess I didn't want
to be left out of the fun.

36:39.948 --> 36:43.285
You're gonna play?

36:43.285 --> 36:44.912
After all the times you told me

36:44.912 --> 36:46.288
the game was a trap,
that it was a con...

36:46.288 --> 36:47.539
- It is.
- Then why are you here?

36:47.539 --> 36:48.874
'Cause maybe
it's my only option.

36:48.874 --> 36:50.417
What the hell
does that even mean?

36:50.417 --> 36:52.294
Look, you're the one
that said that best friends

36:52.294 --> 36:53.712
are supposed
to support each other.

36:53.712 --> 36:54.755
Supposed to support,
not compete with.

36:54.755 --> 36:56.757
Okay, we can play together.

36:56.757 --> 36:59.301
There is no together in Panic.

36:59.301 --> 37:01.678
It's you or me, remember?
One winner only?

37:01.678 --> 37:03.764
I mean, God,
you can't be serious.

37:03.764 --> 37:05.641
Y-You're scared of everything.

37:05.641 --> 37:08.185
I mean, you won't even
get high with me.

37:08.185 --> 37:10.395
You can't even sneak into
a movie theater. I mean...

37:10.395 --> 37:13.649
Come on. You can't
really think you're gonna win.

37:13.649 --> 37:16.068
No one is that dumb.

37:16.068 --> 37:18.904
- No, of course not.
- [Diggins] Last call
for contestants!

37:18.904 --> 37:20.572
But I've got nothing to lose.

37:32.668 --> 37:36.922
[Heather] Once upon a time,
there was a girl made of dirt.

37:36.922 --> 37:39.383
[Natalie] Heather!

37:39.383 --> 37:41.802
Heather, come back!

37:41.802 --> 37:45.764
[Heather] She lived in a town
full of stone people.

37:45.764 --> 37:51.436
"You're nothing," they all said
to the girl made of dirt.

37:51.436 --> 37:54.064
- "Nothing."
- [cheering]

37:54.064 --> 37:56.066
- Hey.
- Jesus.

37:56.066 --> 37:58.276
- Where the hell have you been?
- I-I had to pee, okay?

37:58.276 --> 38:01.071
- Calm down.
- Calm down? Heather!

38:03.156 --> 38:04.866
[Heather] Every night,
the girl made of dirt

38:04.866 --> 38:08.495
would talk to the wind...

38:08.495 --> 38:11.123
and the wind would only sigh.

38:13.875 --> 38:17.170
The girl was lonely.

38:17.170 --> 38:20.132
[Diggins] Contestant 23.

38:20.132 --> 38:22.551
State your name.

38:22.551 --> 38:25.345
- Who is that?
- That's, uh, Heather Nill.

38:25.345 --> 38:27.347
She lives in Two Pines,
across from Ruby Anne's sister.

38:27.347 --> 38:29.433
Hey, look, all you have to do
is throw in some food stamps

38:29.433 --> 38:31.727
- and that'll get her moving.
- Shut the fuck up.

38:31.727 --> 38:33.520
[laughter]

38:33.520 --> 38:35.814
[Sofia] Seriously, how long
are we supposed to wait for?

38:35.814 --> 38:38.233
- Heather, come down!
- Heather.

38:38.233 --> 38:39.901
Come on, Heather.

38:54.791 --> 38:58.003
- [cheering, clapping]
- [girl] Fucking go.

38:58.003 --> 39:00.756
- Come on, Heather!
- She's not gonna do it.
She's not gonna do it.

39:00.756 --> 39:02.758
♪ ♪

39:27.074 --> 39:29.076
♪ ♪

39:43.423 --> 39:45.425
♪ ♪

39:51.556 --> 39:53.100
Oh, my God. Drew.

39:55.018 --> 39:57.145
What is she doing?

39:57.145 --> 39:59.064
She's playing.

40:01.066 --> 40:05.529
[Heather] Then one day,
there was a storm.

40:05.529 --> 40:09.491
It rained for days and days.

40:09.491 --> 40:15.038
The water climbed and climbed,
higher and higher.

40:18.041 --> 40:20.418
♪ ♪

40:22.712 --> 40:24.256
[girl] Don't do it!

40:24.256 --> 40:26.883
Oh, my God.
She's going to Devil's Drop.

40:29.678 --> 40:32.722
[Heather] Soon,
the stone people were trapped,

40:32.722 --> 40:35.350
begging the wind
to take them to safety.

40:35.350 --> 40:37.894
[Diggins] Are you sure
you want to do this, Heather?

40:37.894 --> 40:40.272
No harm in turning back.

40:40.272 --> 40:41.648
Uh, you know, you've al...

40:41.648 --> 40:43.066
you've already made
a real statement.

40:45.026 --> 40:48.071
[Heather] But the stone people
were too heavy to carry.

40:48.071 --> 40:50.073
[wind gusting]

40:51.908 --> 40:55.370
Then the wind spotted
the girl made of dirt.

40:55.370 --> 40:57.873
She would be no problem
to carry.

41:00.125 --> 41:01.293
[boy] Come down, Heather!

41:01.293 --> 41:03.295
[overlapping shouting]

41:03.295 --> 41:05.755
- [girl] Don't be stupid!
- Will somebody get her down?

41:05.755 --> 41:09.134
[overlapping shouting continues]

41:09.134 --> 41:10.510
[boy] Come on, Heather!

41:10.510 --> 41:12.846
[boy 2] What do you got
to prove? Come on!

41:15.182 --> 41:19.269
Contestant 23,
s-state your name.

41:21.730 --> 41:24.191
Heather...

41:24.191 --> 41:27.235
Nill.

41:27.235 --> 41:28.987
Heather Nill.

41:30.989 --> 41:33.325
So the wind opened its arms.

41:33.325 --> 41:36.536
And the girl made of dirt
turned to air...

41:40.874 --> 41:42.876
♪ ♪

41:45.712 --> 41:46.922
...and flew.

41:48.965 --> 41:50.967
♪ ♪

42:19.996 --> 42:21.998
♪ ♪

42:51.027 --> 42:53.029
♪ ♪

43:23.059 --> 43:25.061
